Angular architecture is based on a **component-driven, modular, event-based** structure where every feature of the application is organized into components, services, modules, and templates. Data flows through bindings, and Angular manages rendering using its change-detection system.

![Image](https://v2.angular.io/resources/images/devguide/architecture/overview2.png?utm_source=chatgpt.com)

![Image](https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20230910120905/archi.png?utm_source=chatgpt.com)

**Core Parts of Angular Architecture**

**1. Modules (NgModule)**
Modules group related components, directives, and services.
`app.module.ts` is the root module of every Angular app.

**2. Components**
The basic building blocks of Angular.
Each component has:

* `.ts` (logic)
* `.html` (template)
* `.css` (styles)
* `.spec.ts` (tests)

**3. Templates**
Define the view using HTML + Angular directives like `*ngIf`, `*ngFor`.

**4. Metadata**
Decorators (`@Component`, `@NgModule`) tell Angular how to process classes.

**5. Data Binding**
Communication between component and UI:

* Interpolation `{{ }}`
* Property binding `[ ]`
* Event binding `( )`
* Two-way binding `[(ngModel)]`

**6. Directives**
Custom instructions to modify DOM behavior.
Types:

* Structural (`*ngIf`, `*ngFor`)
* Attribute (`ngClass`, `ngStyle`)

**7. Services**
Contain business logic, HTTP calls, shared data.
Injected using Angular’s **Dependency Injection** system.

**8. Dependency Injection (DI)**
Automatically provides instances of services to components.

**9. Routing**
Maps URLs to components to enable single-page application navigation.

**Text Diagram**

```
               Angular App
                     │
          ┌──────────┴──────────┐
          │                     │
       Module                Component
          │                     │
   Declarations           Template + Class
          │                     │
       Services  ← DI →     Business Logic
          │                     │
       Routing  ←──────→  Navigation
```

